      "id": "PopularPost58809",
      "post_content": "Back when Planeshift was new, a couple of people in my casual play group were playing a U/B control deck which included this, [Warped Devotion](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Warped Devotion) and [Megrim](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Megrim) as a wacky win condition. The rest of it was centred around counter, bounce and discard spells - and of course, the Invasion block included neat things like [Recoil](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Recoil). It was very slow but because the average skill level of the group wasn't so high, it didn't do too badly.  \n  \nOf course, this was an era in which [Tranquility](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tranquility) was a staple card and [Tranquil Grove](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tranquil Grove) was part of the core set. Once the mono-green beatdown players of the group figured out what to do, it was curtains for the poor old Sunken Hope deck and [Blastoderm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blastoderm) returned to being the dominant threat in our small group.",
      "posted_by": "HeavyElectricity",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost58809\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">Back when Planeshift was new, a couple of people in my casual play group were playing a U/B control deck which included this, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Warped Devotion\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Warped Devotion\">Warped Devotion</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Megrim\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Megrim\">Megrim</a> as a wacky win condition. The rest of it was centred around counter, bounce and discard spells - and of course, the Invasion block included neat things like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Recoil\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Recoil\">Recoil</a>. It was very slow but because the average skill level of the group wasn't so high, it didn't do too badly.<br/><br/>Of course, this was an era in which <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Tranquility\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tranquility\">Tranquility</a> was a staple card and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Tranquil Grove\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tranquil Grove\">Tranquil Grove</a> was part of the core set. Once the mono-green beatdown players of the group figured out what to do, it was curtains for the poor old Sunken Hope deck and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Blastoderm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blastoderm\">Blastoderm</a> returned to being the dominant threat in our small group.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '5